### ðŸŽ¯ **PWA ENHANCEMENT PLAN**

This issue outlines the plan to elevate the existing Progressive Web App (PWA) functionality to meet enterprise-grade standards. This initiative builds upon our strong SEO foundation and will significantly improve the mobile experience, performance, and offline capabilities of the CV platform.

### **Current PWA Implementation**

-   **`manifest.json`**: A basic web app manifest is in place.
-   **`sw.js`**: A service worker with a simple caching strategy is implemented.

### **Proposed Enhancements**

#### 1. **Comprehensive Web App Manifest (`manifest.json`)**

The existing `manifest.json` will be updated to include a more complete set of PWA features, including icons, screenshots, and categories.

**Current `manifest.json`:**

```json
{
    "name": "Adrian Wedd - CV",
    "short_name": "Adrian Wedd",
    "start_url": ".",
    "display": "standalone",
    "background_color": "#fff",
    "description": "A CV for Adrian Wedd.",
    "icons": []
}
```

**Proposed `manifest.json`:**

```json
{
  "name": "Adrian Wedd - AI Engineer & Software Architect",
  "short_name": "Adrian Wedd CV",
  "description": "Professional CV showcasing AI engineering and software architecture expertise",
  "start_url": "/cv/",
  "display": "standalone",
  "background_color": "#1a1a1a",
  "theme_color": "#1a1a1a",
  "icons": [
    {
      "src": "assets/icons/icon-192.png",
      "sizes": "192x192",
      "type": "image/png",
      "purpose": "any maskable"
    },
    {
